29/09/2003
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- UNMIK head Harri Holkeri travels to Belgrade on Monday (29 September).
He will meet with high-ranking republican and federal government representatives, in preparation for the start of dialogue between Belgrade and Pristina.
The talks are scheduled for 14 October in Vienna.
Holkeri, who is to oversee the dialogue, is trying to convince Serbia-Montenegro President Svetozar Marovic and Serbian Prime Minister Zoran Zivkovic to lead the Belgrade delegation.
Holkeri has already met with leading Kosovo government representatives to discuss Pristina's position regarding the talks.
(B92, BBC, Tanjug - 28/09/03)
